<br>
You're safe from agro for about 15s after zone-in.  However, this 15s starts when the server thinks you're zoned-in, not when you think it.  If you have a very fast zoning system, you can zone in and run about without any agro for a long time.  For instance, I can zone into SG and run across the zone to WW without agro because I zone fast.  I don't think I could use that to get to Trak, though.  So, my bet is on DA.<br>
<br>
Maxvs, you can zone in safely.  However, there is no safe spot for a non-FD'er to easily obtain a target for bind-sight.  There are two sets of doors.  It's possible to open the first set safely (not a sure thing, but possible).  In order to open the second set, you have to get past some guards.  You can't do that as a ranger and nothing roams through the second set for bind-sight.  A bard would be much better for bind-sight hopping.  I'm betting someone left a corpse in ST.  Bards can find corpse, then bind-sight to that.<br>
<br>
BTW, I haven't used one in forever, but if a chipped bone rod puts the nearest corpse in your target, then you could do that too.  You could also use an eye of zomm (stalking probes) to zip in past the doors to get a target for your bind-sight hop.  There are doors further in, but there are also roamers you can ride through them.  This would be enough to take you in past the library, but that's about as far as you can go (maybe 1/3 of the way to FA and warders). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaxvs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maxvs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 3:19:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2804.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have no idea ..</span><hr size=1> Ummm...<br>
